## How OMF and dOSPO Relate

OMF and the [Decentralized Open Source Program Office (dOSPO)](https://github.com/opensourcecowboy/dospo-architecture) together form a complete institutional model for governing and sustaining open source infrastructure in decentralized ecosystems.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  dOSPO  — Governance Primitive              │
│  Defines HOW ecosystems coordinate and      │
│  govern: policy domains, governance bodies, │
│  execution structure, mandate constraints   │
└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────┘
                      │
                      ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  OMF  — Operational Framework               │
│  Defines WHAT coordination bodies execute:  │
│  programs, funding instruments, portfolio   │
│  stewardship, maintainer sustainment        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**OMF can operate without a dOSPO.** When no formal coordination layer exists, OMF deploys directly through whatever accountable governance structure the ecosystem already possesses — a foundation committee, a multisig, an elected committee, or an independent operator. The minimum requirement is identical in both cases: governance authority to authorize programs, a funded budget, transparent reporting, and a portfolio review cadence.

