## The Five-Layer Stack

| Layer | Role | OMF's Position |
|---|---|---|
| **On-Chain Governance** | Strategic priorities, treasury authorization, binding decisions | Provides mandate and budget |
| **Policy & Coordination** | Non-binding coordination, community standards, dOSPO | Optional layer above OMF |
| **Infrastructure Stewardship** | Translates decisions into sustained programs | **This is where OMF operates** |
| **Maintainer Layer** | Individuals and teams maintaining infrastructure projects | Primary beneficiaries |
| **Infrastructure Layer** | The software, protocols, libraries, tools | The asset all layers sustain |

OMF is not a middleman — it is a structural interface. It translates governance intent into operational action, and operational outcomes into data governance uses to make better resource allocation decisions.

