## Program Portfolio

Each program addresses a distinct dimension of infrastructure sustainability and can be implemented independently. Begin with one or two and expand as capacity develops.

| Program | Purpose | Primary Funding Instrument | Reference Model |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Maintainer Retainer** | Ongoing support tied to maintenance responsibility, not deliverables | Continuity-oriented | Protocol Guild, Cardano POSM, Sentry |
| **Code Bounties** | Funded delivery of specific features, fixes, or security work | Delivery-oriented | Gitcoin, GitHub Secure OSS Fund |
| **Contributor Pathways** | Structured mentorship to grow the future maintainer pipeline | Delivery-oriented + Continuity supplement | CNCF LFX Mentorship (25 maintainers since 2020) |
| **Operational Support** | Admin services: security audits, legal review, documentation | Delivery-oriented | GitHub Secure Fund cohort model |
| **Incubation** | Structured support for early-stage critical projects | Delivery-oriented → Continuity transition | STA milestone contracts |
| **Resilience Programs** | Succession planning, bus-factor reduction, knowledge documentation | All three instruments | Kubernetes NGINX failure case |

> **The full system**: Contributor Pathways grow the maintainer pool that sustains the Retainer program. Operational Support reduces burden, making Retainer support go further. Resilience Programs preserve the institutional knowledge Retainer programs help accumulate.

