## Getting Started

### Step 1 — Assess readiness
Does your ecosystem have at least one of the five structural failures OMF is designed to address? (Dependency risk at scale, incident coordination latency, funding mismatch, governance gap, missing contributor pipeline.) If yes, proceed.

### Step 2 — Conduct a dependency audit
Before standing up any program, map your ecosystem's dependency graph. Use the 60-day audit walkthrough in [`templates/dependency-audit-template.md`](templates/dependency-audit-template.md). This is the non-negotiable first step — everything else flows from knowing which infrastructure is at risk.

### Step 3 — Start narrow
You do not need to deploy the full program portfolio. The minimum viable OMF is a dependency audit, governance authorization, and a single sustainment program — typically a small Retainer cohort (2–5 projects) plus one Contributor Pathway cohort. First-year cost estimate for a mid-sized Web3 ecosystem: $280–570K.

### Step 4 — Get governance authorization
Use [`templates/governance-proposal-template.md`](templates/governance-proposal-template.md) to submit a budget request and program charter to your governance body. Programs must not self-authorize.

### Step 5 — Launch, report, renew
Run the program. Publish quarterly transparency reports using [`templates/quarterly-report-template.md`](templates/quarterly-report-template.md). Conduct a mid-point governance review. Make renewal decisions based on outcomes, not advocacy.

### First 12 Months Reference Roadmap

| Month | Action | Estimated Cost |
|---|---|---|
| 1–2 | Dependency audit: map critical dependencies, score centrality, identify top-20 risks | ~$15–30K |
| 2–3 | Governance proposal: OMF pilot budget (Retainers + 1 Pathway cohort) | ~$5–10K |
| 3–6 | Launch Retainer program (3–5 projects, 6-month initial); launch first contributor cohort | ~$200–400K/yr |
| 6–9 | Mid-point review: publish outcome data; governance review of retainer performance | ~$10K |
| 9–12 | Renewal cycle: evidence-based renewal; add Resilience programs if capacity allows | ~$50–100K |

